{\footnote # IDH_COBOL_02}
{\footnote $ COBOL - STRUCTURE D'UN PROGRAMME}
{\footnote K COBOL structure programme;IDENTIFICATION DIVISION;ENVIRONMENT DIVISION;DATA DIVISION;PROCEDURE DIVISION;PROGRAM-ID;FILE-CONTROL;LINKAGE SECTION;WORKING-STORAGE}
\b\fs24 STRUCTURE D'UN PROGRAMME \b0\fs20\par
\par
Un programme COBOL est structure en quatre DIVISIONS dans\par
un ordre fixe :\par
\par
{\f1   IDENTIFICATION DIVISION    (obligatoire)}\par
{\f1   ENVIRONMENT DIVISION       (optionnelle)}\par
{\f1   DATA DIVISION              (optionnelle)}\par
{\f1   PROCEDURE DIVISION         (obligatoire)}\par
\par
\par
\b 2.1 Exemple complet \b0\par
\par
{\f1   IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.}\par
{\f1   PROGRAM-ID. BONJOUR.}\par
{\f1   AUTHOR. SYLVAIN.}\par
\par
{\f1   ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.}\par
{\f1   CONFIGURATION SECTION.}\par
{\f1   SOURCE-COMPUTER. IBM-PC.}\par
\par
{\f1   DATA DIVISION.}\par
{\f1   WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.}\par
{\f1   01 WS-MESSAGE PIC X(20) VALUE "Bonjour, monde!".}\par
\par
{\f1   PROCEDURE DIVISION.}\par
{\f1   MAIN-PARA.}\par
{\f1     DISPLAY WS-MESSAGE.}\par
{\f1     STOP RUN.}\par
\par
\par
\b 2.2 IDENTIFICATION DIVISION \b0\par
\par
Decrit le programme (metadonnees) :\par
\par
{\f1   IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.}\par
{\f1   PROGRAM-ID. MONPROG.}\par
{\f1   AUTHOR. JEAN DUPONT.}\par
{\f1   DATE-WRITTEN. 14/05/2026.}\par
{\f1   DATE-COMPILED.}\par
{\f1   REMARKS. Programme exemple.}\par
\par
\par
\b 2.3 ENVIRONMENT DIVISION \b0\par
\par
Decrit l'environnement materiel/logiciel :\par
\par
{\f1   ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.}\par
{\f1   CONFIGURATION SECTION.}\par
{\f1     SOURCE-COMPUTER. IBM-PC.}\par
{\f1     OBJECT-COMPUTER. IBM-PC.}\par
{\f1   INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.}\par
{\f1     FILE-CONTROL.}\par
{\f1       SELECT CLIENTS ASSIGN TO "CLIENTS.DAT"}\par
{\f1         ORGANIZATION IS INDEXED}\par
{\f1         ACCESS MODE  IS DYNAMIC}\par
{\f1         RECORD KEY   IS CLI-CODE.}\par
\par
\par
\b 2.4 DATA DIVISION \b0\par
\par
Declare toutes les donnees :\par
\par
{\f1   DATA DIVISION.}\par
{\f1   FILE SECTION.}\par
{\f1     FD CLIENTS.}\par
{\f1     01 CLIENT-REC.}\par
{\f1        05 CLI-CODE    PIC 9(5).}\par
{\f1        05 CLI-NOM     PIC X(30).}\par
{\f1        05 CLI-SOLDE   PIC S9(7)V99 COMP-3.}\par
\par
{\f1   WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.}\par
{\f1     01 WS-COMPTEUR    PIC 9(4) VALUE ZERO.}\par
{\f1     01 WS-TOTAL       PIC 9(9)V99 VALUE ZERO.}\par
\par
{\f1   LINKAGE SECTION.}\par
{\f1     01 LK-PARAM       PIC X(80).}\par
\par
\par
\b 2.5 PROCEDURE DIVISION \b0\par
\par
Contient le code executable :\par
\par
{\f1   PROCEDURE DIVISION [USING LK-PARAM].}\par
{\f1   MAIN-PARA.}\par
{\f1     PERFORM INIT-PARA.}\par
{\f1     PERFORM TRAIT-PARA UNTIL FIN-FICHIER.}\par
{\f1     PERFORM FIN-PARA.}\par
{\f1     STOP RUN.}\par
\par
{\f1   INIT-PARA.}\par
{\f1     OPEN INPUT CLIENTS.}\par
\par
{\f1   TRAIT-PARA.}\par
{\f1     READ CLIENTS AT END MOVE "OUI" TO FIN-FICHIER.}\par
\par
{\f1   FIN-PARA.}\par
{\f1     CLOSE CLIENTS.}\par
\par
\par
\par
