{\footnote # IDH_COBOL_05}
{\footnote $ COBOL - PROCEDURE DIVISION - INSTRUCTIONS DE BASE}
{\footnote K COBOL instructions base;MOVE;DISPLAY;ACCEPT;COMPUTE;ADD;SUBTRACT;MULTIPLY;DIVIDE;STRING;UNSTRING;INSPECT;INITIALIZE}
\b\fs24 PROCEDURE DIVISION - INSTRUCTIONS DE BASE \b0\fs20\par
\par
\par
\b 5.1 MOVE - affectation \b0\par
\par
{\f1   MOVE 0 TO WS-COMPTEUR.}\par
{\f1   MOVE "Inconnu" TO WS-NOM.}\par
{\f1   MOVE CLI-NOM TO WS-NOM.}\par
{\f1   MOVE CORRESPONDING REC-A TO REC-B.}\par
{\f1   MOVE SPACES TO WS-LIGNE.}\par
{\f1   MOVE ZEROS  TO WS-TOTAL.}\par
\par
\par
\b 5.2 DISPLAY / ACCEPT - I/O console \b0\par
\par
{\f1   DISPLAY "Resultat: " WS-TOTAL.}\par
{\f1   DISPLAY "Valeur: " X UPON CONSOLE.}\par
{\f1   ACCEPT WS-INPUT.}\par
{\f1   ACCEPT WS-DATE FROM DATE.       (* AAMMJJ *)}\par
{\f1   ACCEPT WS-TIME FROM TIME.       (* HHMMSScc *)}\par
\par
\par
\b 5.3 COMPUTE - calcul algebrique \b0\par
\par
{\f1   COMPUTE WS-TOTAL = WS-PRIX * WS-QTE.}\par
{\f1   COMPUTE WS-MOY ROUNDED = WS-SOMME / WS-N.}\par
\par
\par
\b 5.4 ADD / SUBTRACT / MULTIPLY / DIVIDE \b0\par
\par
{\f1   ADD 1 TO WS-COMPTEUR.}\par
{\f1   ADD WS-A WS-B GIVING WS-C.}\par
{\f1   SUBTRACT WS-DEDUCTION FROM WS-BRUT GIVING WS-NET.}\par
{\f1   MULTIPLY WS-PRIX BY WS-QTE GIVING WS-TOTAL.}\par
{\f1   DIVIDE WS-SOMME BY WS-N GIVING WS-MOY ROUNDED.}\par
{\f1   DIVIDE 7 INTO WS-X GIVING WS-Q REMAINDER WS-R.}\par
\par
\par
\b 5.5 STRING / UNSTRING \b0\par
\par
Concatenation :\par
\par
{\f1   STRING "Bonjour " DELIMITED BY SIZE}\par
{\f1          WS-NOM    DELIMITED BY SPACES}\par
{\f1          INTO      WS-MESSAGE.}\par
\par
Decoupage :\par
\par
{\f1   UNSTRING WS-LIGNE DELIMITED BY ","}\par
{\f1     INTO WS-CHAMP1 WS-CHAMP2 WS-CHAMP3.}\par
\par
\par
\b 5.6 INSPECT \b0\par
\par
Comptage et remplacement de caracteres :\par
\par
{\f1   INSPECT WS-TEXTE TALLYING WS-N FOR ALL "A".}\par
{\f1   INSPECT WS-TEXTE REPLACING ALL "X" BY "Y".}\par
\par
\par
\b 5.7 INITIALIZE \b0\par
\par
Met les zones a leur valeur par defaut (zero pour numerique,\par
espace pour alphanumerique) :\par
\par
{\f1   INITIALIZE CLIENT-REC.}\par
\par
\par
\par
